    • Method Detail

      • unsubscribeAll

        public void unsubscribeAll​(MkvChainListener lner)
        Removes all the subscriptions made with the specified MkvChainListener.

        Once this method is called the listener is no longer used by the API to notify updates.
        This operation is equivalent to calling MkvChain.unsubscribe(MkvChainListener) for every single chain subscribed with the specified listener.

        Parameters:
        lner - the listener.
        See Also:
        MkvChain.unsubscribe(MkvChainListener)

      • unsubscribeAll

        public void unsubscribeAll​(MkvRecordListener lner)
        Removes all the subscriptions made with the specified MkvRecordListener.

        Once this method is called the listener is no longer used by the API to notify updates.
        This operation is equivalent to calling MkvRecord.unsubscribe(MkvRecordListener) for each record or pattern subscribed with the specified listener.

        Parameters:
        lner - the listener.
        See Also:
        MkvRecord.unsubscribe(MkvRecordListener)

      • unsubscribeAll

        public void unsubscribeAll()
        Removes all subscription.

        Once this method is called all chain and record listeners are no longer used by the API to notify updates.
        This method can't be used with persistent subscriptions .
